INSERT INTO `csiemployees` VALUES ('EVYZACA','murugesan.m@ericsson.com','Bangalore','ERATBHA','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn RNAM','','','','Professionalism: It is basically the standards, principles and codes of conduct enshrining rigorous ethical and moral obligations within oneself which prepare members of the profession with the particular knowledge and skills necessary to perform the role of that professions typically agreed upon and maintained.\r\nRespect: It is a positive feeling of esteem or deference for a person or other entity, and also specific actions and conduct representative of that esteem. Respect can be a specific feeling of regard for the actual qualities of the one respected. It is to act with integrity, caring for people, communities and the environment as well as the way we value our people, encourage their development and reward their performance. Mutual respect is the recognition of the equal worth of each individual, with full utilization of our diverse backgrounds, interests and strengths.\r\nPerseverance: It is commitment, hard work, patience and endurance. It is being able to bear difficulties calmly and with complete ownership and responsibility. It is the act or quality of holding to a course of action, belief, or purpose. Sticking to a purpose or a goal and never giving up is another way to express this. To try and try again, no matter what obstacles are placed demonstrates perseverance.','','','','','','','','',1,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 09:43:09','Pending'),('EPTUVYY','s.a.karthikeyan@ericsson.com','Bangalore','ECHASHH','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn RNAM CA 2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-04-30 03:20:05','Pending'),('EATREPS','atresh.p.s@ericsson.com','Bangalore','ESKPKUM','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA Billing 4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-04-30 06:36:49','Pending'),('EKUMMUN','munish.kumar@ericsson.com','Noida','EGANVAI','BUGS GSI OSS Adaptation','Once you realize that you\'re in something that you\'ve always wanted and you don\'t want to lose it, you behave differently. And that means the integrity, the #Professionalism, and knowing what\'s right from wrong and still making choices that you probably wouldn\'t have made','We are sun and moon. we are sea and land. It is not our purpose to become each other; it is to recognize each other, to learn to see the other and #Respect him for what he is: each the other\'s opposite and complement.','#Perseverance is the hard work you do after you get tired of doing the hard work you already did.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',5,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-04-30 06:46:16','Pending'),('ESIAMSI','amit.g.singh@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ENANMOH','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA EMM EMA','','','','E/// values are its soul and the way people across region carry with them is simple awesome.\r\nAn employee of E/// global citizen. Anywhere in E/// office, you feel at home in terms of work culture, delivery model, trainings,certifications, IPM etc. I am fortunate to be part of this journey and also over a period of time people of this company have instilled my faith in its values i.e. Professionalism, Respect and perseverance. I too imbibed this values in due course of time.\r\nMy story about E/// core values is from one of my assignment with Digicel Martinique (A carribean island) for system live upgrade. Due to some reasons, a task that was suppose to be completed in couple of weeks time has actually taken 4 months to deliver. \r\nWhen I get this opportunity in first week of June, I had enormous responsibility of gaining customer confidence and also instilling faith of customer in E/// Global delivery model. \r\nIf I capture my experience in terms of E/// code values, it goes like:\r\nProfessionalism\r\nI collected as much as information from previous engineer, line management, design unit, CPM and also from customer. My whole objective was to identify the gaps and start working on same. Before starting the actual work I wanted to gain confidence of customer and E/// project manager as region was not ready to take this up unless we have chance of ~100% success.\r\nAs a professional consultant, I did the analysis, take references, analyse customer IT environment and ask as many question as possible to reach a point where I am sure that root cause of previous failure is pretty clear to everyone and next execution will not fail.\r\nRespect\r\nIn due course of time I developed a good rapport and gain their confidence about successful execution. Prepared details solution strategy with clearly mentionedc time-line of deliverables and fall-back approach with minimum impact. This has helped me in gain customer confidence and also reflection of my understanding of customer problem and pain areas.\r\nPerseverance\r\nI had faced different kind of problems in information gathering, strict time-line and travel related issues. But all this while my focus was on gain customer confidence. Putting faith of people involved in our global delivery model. My previous experience and faith shown by people around me has been really helpful. In my professional journey this was first moment when most of us were not sure about outcome but I was sure about it. Finally when I did it successfully, it was one such moment that one cherish throughout their life.\r\nI am glad that I share this with you all and may be it will inspire someone to  have his faith in E/// values. I would like to conclude this story with following\r\nexerpt from this journey:\r\n\"Thanks Amit for your great support and recover back customer confidence in our global delivery Capabilities as Ericsson. It was worth it all the preparation meetings we had to go right this time. \"\r\n--Juan Paz, CD Prime Driver OSS BSS Media App','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,6,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 08:53:44','Pending'),('ESACUPP','sachin.uppal@ericsson.com','Noida','ESOBSAR','BUGS GSI TV & Media',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'EIRSAHM',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-04-30 06:52:47','Pending'),('EKASTSR','kasthuri.rengan.srinivasan@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EMAPADM','BUGS GSI PDU ACNT 2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-04-30 06:58:07','Pending'),('ETAAKAA','tamanna.kataria@ericsson.com','Noida','EANTYAG','BUGS GSI DU','Being Human while in Office\r\n-------------------------------------\r\nHaving worked in IT services Industry for about 6 years,i have seen Professionalism is never a MUST personality trait.But here in Ericsson ,its one of the core value and having completed close to 7 months in Ericsson,It clearly felt that it is not a forced attribute but is a trait among many people i have worked with and its really appreciating.\r\n\r\nOne day,in my team there was some defect that was found out in Code and the reponsible coder was on sick leave.\r\nWe needed to submit the defect fix the next day and it was really critical.To control the situation,Leads together with some other team member sat till late in office ,worked on weekend to deliver the defect fix sucessfully.\r\n\r\nWhen i got to know this , It really arose RESPECT fo those leads for the PROFESSIONALISM they have shown in time of crisis.\r\nLater on we got a Team Appreciation also for this Enhancement.So it was the teamwork that generated this win-win po','\r\nRespect is earned not yearned!!\r\n\r\nRESPECT to me not only means giving gratitude to elders but is something that will create your impression for years to come.It is very rightly said U cant buy it U earn Respect!!\r\n\r\nRespect can never be artifical or man made.It is something that comes from within and that is only possible when you are such a person that knows that What he gives is what he gets Back!','Way to Success via Perseverence\r\n\r\nIt is rightly said \"Great works are performed not by strength but by perseverance.\"\r\n\r\nSo for a company to work effectively One must learn the art of Perseverance!!','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',9,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 05:34:38','Pending'),('ENAHCHI','naresh.chandani@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EKAMSEH','BUGS GSI Service Enablmnt Unit 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,10,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-04-30 13:16:26','Pending'),('EPPPRRR','p.ravichandran@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EMMMAAA','BUGS GSI BSS Adaptation',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,11,'ESURASI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 08:11:56','Pending'),('EDHOMAN','manoj.kumar.dhote@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EMQQRUV','BUGS GSI TV & Media Unit 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,12,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 09:14:21','Pending'),('EABSVAR','abs.varkey@ericsson.com','Pune','EKUSGHO','BUGS GSI E2E Architecture Group 3',NULL,NULL,'We had an overwhelming situation on a Greenfield MVNO implementation. Ericsson was engaged midway as the Prime SI to take over the entire E2E program from the existing SI’s.Taking ownership of the Program without structured Requirements and Vendor commitments/Contracts was highly risky for Ericsson.\r\nEricsson took the risk. We believed that with a structured approach and hard work it was not an impossible task. Post creation of the Requirement framework & tool, the tedious task of mapping over 2500 requirements was undertaken. Almost a kin to hammering a stone hundred times until it finally yields, the team kept going day after day. \r\nThe client was ecstatic. In their words - “This Framework and tool has exceeded our expectations and we appreciate the enormous efforts put in populating, analyzing & mapping our requirements & Business Processes” Perseverance is many short races one after another. Impossible things take a little longer. With perseverance, all things are attainable. \r\n','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',13,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-12 09:10:30','Pending'),('EGANVAI','ganesh.vaidyanathan@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EMMMAAA','BUGS GSI OSS Adaptation',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,14,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 10:14:16','Pending'),('EAADMAD','irshad.m.ahmad@ericsson.com','Gurgaon','EGASHAH','BUGS GSI CD ADM & IT-MS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 10:47:27','Pending'),('EANITPA','anita.pal@ericsson.com','PUNE','EDEKATK','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA Billing 1','I do not like heavy words in life but “Professionalism” is one with which I connect myself. The meaning of may be different for different people as they perceive but let me explain what and how of this for me. I feel that being professional does not mean to always work related to project/ assignment but it means also to take active part in off the job activities sponsored/ organized by organization. As we know “All Work and No Play Makes Jack a Dull Boy” so professionalism saves me from becoming a Dull and I achieve this being active participant in the organizational activities as much as possible and makes me a true professional. It also helps me to stretch myself sometimes but ultimately it helps me in realization of my true potential in a professional way. I feel that Professionalism is also a contributing factor in making the true human beings for society and this reminds me Albert Einstein, ““Try not to become a man of success but rather try to become a man of value.”',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',16,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-12 05:33:20','Pending'),('EMMMAAA','muthukumaran.a@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EDASSAB','BUGS GSI Adaptation Centre',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,17,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 11:51:26','Pending'),('ESRIVMU','srivatsan.muralidharan@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EMAPADM','BUGS GSI PDU ACNT 2',NULL,NULL,'Dealt with a Tough Customer:\r\n1. I was assigned with a HIGH severity issue from an US customer.\r\n2. The issue was very tricky and capturing of logs were difficult too.\r\n3. Though the customer tried their best to share us the logs, but that was not enough to narrow down the root cause.\r\n4. The issue was discussed to be escalated from HIGH to HOT.\r\n5. To avoid making it a HOT issue, I chaired multiple calls with Customer team.\r\n6. Teaming with few of my colleagues and I proposed a DEBUG patch to get right logs.\r\n7. Customer was not OK in that, as they were afraid of call-loss of millions due to REBOOT and what if the DEBUG fails.\r\n8. Again I did multiple rounds of discussions and negotiated them to agree for DEBUG patch.\r\n9. Stretching a bit more with team, we found Actual root cause which made HIGH to MEDIUM & no with need of DEBUG.\r\nOn this assignment, I felt, I have displayed a good amount of perseverance to instill confidence on the customer and thereby closing the issue by effective','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',18,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-14 11:28:29','Pending'),('EYOGESW','k.yogeswaran@ericsson.com','Chennai','ESRISET','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn TV CA 2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,19,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 12:08:58','Pending'),('ETHANGA','p.thangamani@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','ESHAHHA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,'EIRSAHM',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 12:55:56','Pending'),('EGAHSHM','ganesh.shanmugham@ericsson.com','Chennai','EMOHVIJ','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn ECE CA 2',NULL,NULL,'Perseverance - a trait that travels throughout our life...exhibited in the toughest phases of our lives...It makes me achieve what i have being dreaming about...it brought out the plans in paper to visible success in my life...the best practice to stay in the battle and never give up until i have tasted victory...','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',21,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 10:16:01','Pending'),('EEHIIJM','rajesh.v@ericsson.com','Chennai','EGAUTDH','BUGS GSI Sprint NIM',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,22,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-04 14:07:33','Pending'),('EKAIPAT','kailash.chandra.patel@ericsson.com','PUNE','EGVNRED','BUGS GSI SDC ADM Common Services',NULL,NULL,'It was one fine day but final day of the last year students in the Gurukul. Everyone was thinking what will we do after this and are we equipped with all the necessary learning/ tools to survive in the real world? As we know that Guru is the person who shows us light and here too one such Guru realized the pain of his disciples and asked to all of them “You all are perfect & can achieve your aim but there is one final teaching is left and before that I want you all to go & bring water for me in your basket from the nearest river”. \r\nMost of the students tried 2-3 times but could not hold the water in the basket. 2-3 tried for 6-7 times but failed and returned to Gurukul. Miracle happened to one student who tried and tried till the time wood sticks got widen and stuck to each other to hold the water. Guru Ji gave him blessings and gave the final message to everyone “Try continuously the work at hand and you will achieve success - Perseverance”. I am proud that it is one of the Core Valu','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EGVNRED/EKAIPAT_Per_1404192782.mp4','Perseverance_From Teaching to Action','','',23,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:34:07','Pending'),('EDHILIP','dhilip.chakravarthy.s@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','ERANANA','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA CRS','','','','My Journey started 4 years back when I joined Ericsson. Even though I was full of energy and excitement, I haven\'t travelled much and I was completely new to telecom. But With Ericsson, I Explored the world of opportunities and Travelled to almost all corners of the world to deliver the service.\r\n\r\nI also got the opportunity to interact with Culturally and linguistically diverse people across the globe.\r\n\r\nI have delivered my projects with complete professionalism, respect and Perseverance. I respect the feelings of customers and my fellow Ericsson colleagues. I always look for quality and speed in all the  deliveries. This made me to be one among the strong workforce in Ericsson who go by the Ethics and provide flawless delivery.\r\n\r\nWith Ericsson, I witnessed the Global imbalance, especially when I travelled to the Ebola hit west African countries, West Indies, UK, Malaysia, Singapore, etc. I started respecting each and every person since I understood that every country and its people are uniquely beautiful.  Also, my it is my parents brought up which made me to see and respect the Spirit of God in the things He has created. All These helped me to obtain utmost customer satisfaction and even now I am in touch with most of the customers. \r\n\r\nI would have left Ericsson 3 yrs back if I didn\'t have the perseverance in me. I can still recollect the memories of 2011 in Algeria, where I was under tremendous pressure most of the time when I had a customer meeting/discussion. It\'s my perseverance which helped me a lot to cope up with pressure and to learn the things faster. Also in places where there are huge diversities like the reunion island, African countries like Benin and Guinea, I struggled a lot, but with my perseverance I was able to bear the hardships and faced the struggle. Later all those turned up to be a success story to me!\r\n\r\nEven now, I\'m changing my Horizon to learn something completely new to me. But I firmly believe that with Ericsson\'s core values I\'ll face the challenge with utmost efficiency. \r\nIt\'s always WE in \"Ericsson\" rather than I!!! ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,24,'ESUJSIH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-08 05:37:20','Pending'),('EKLLOOP','murali.r@ericsson.com','Kolkata','EKATHRA','BUGS GSI IP & Core-UDM','','','','It was a year back, i stepped Ericsson to start my another phase of career, I am the proud chap, when i say it. i mean it! but too soon i realized, having handful of experience with the rivals would not help getting confidence of Ericsson customers who are far more advanced. With the Existing experience thought i was outdated, since then, i started running  it from the beginning, as a fresher, as a learner, as a newbie. I was a rookie that Time..But there was a comeback for me. to get noticed.! i had to chose the path none has taken. Yes, completed two Ericsson certifications in two months in which  one of them is first of its kind. first one in my CD.. Celebrations begun.. but i still felt it is not enough.. to move forward i have more things left doing.. i remember an anonymous quote \"Crawling slowly is better than standing still\". since then i decided to play even minor role to support any complex projects were i  gained knowledge and experience.. One fine day, Wind just turned into a breeze! yes, With the Experience and knowledge i gained all these days helped me to deliver a project successfully which is also first of its kind..  After facing success and failures all these days, when i look back it was perseverance which made me to chase the success after every failures. i believe Perseverance matters..!! It is the attitude that need to be carried through out our life.','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,25,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:57:05','Pending'),('EABBHAN','abhilasha.bhanawat@ericsson.com','Noida','EAGAVIN','BUGS GSI MSDP-AO 4','','','',NULL,'','','','','','','EAGAVIN/EABBHAN_All_688916567.avi','Live Love Ericsson - Live Your Values',26,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-14 11:38:09','Pending'),('EGANVIK','vikram.ganesh@ericsson.com','Gurgaon','EANOMAH','BUGS GSI MSDP-AO',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,27,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-05 06:00:45','Pending'),('EASHIJO','ashish.j.joshi@ericsson.com','Pune','EANNCHI','BUGS GSI TMUS BSS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,28,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-05 06:10:04','Pending'),('EMOHKAP','mohit.kapri@ericsson.com','Pune','EAMIGIR','BUGS GSI CD-BSS Engagement 4','','','','“Hearing about ‘High Performance Culture living /// Values’ event, I wondered if I actually ever had a thought on doing things in a way I serve /// Values too. It appeared to me that ‘Yes’, it’s not just me, but each one of us serve these values in different ways but quite brilliantly on their daily work events.”\r\n\r\nMy story is based out of an event, which inspired my career path into Business Engagement from the hardcore Technical.\r\n\r\nYear 2010, one fine Thursday evening, I got a call with a request if I can be in Bangkok by tomorrow night? I asked the purpose for this travel. After hearing that we are approaching a Telecom Group with whom we have meeting scheduled on coming Monday and my contribution was required from BSCS area, I was for a second astonished thinking how could I be their choice; however on a second thought, why not? I can do things in a right way. So, I made the proper arrangements, started for Mumbai Airport early morning and reached Bangkok Right On Time.\r\nAfter reaching Bangkok, I got to know that it’s not just few of us from India who have reached here, but we have more than 20 other Ericsson Staff as-well from across Globe only for this event. Hearing this, I got to know how big this event is going to be. Again, a bit thrilled if I would be able to make up my part properly & as expected…\r\nThough things were prepared; however we all worked over the weekend again and again refining things for it to look better in front of the customer.\r\nFinal Day has arrived. The event started with introductions. Later we entered a Giant Conference Room wherein we started presenting. Things were moving well until the discussion started happening around BSS Transformation. Everyone had their own thoughts on such Transformations; hence the discussion got stretched and became a little Hot too. After a while, the discussions happening around were started going all above my head. I was trying hard coping up with the vocabulary and even on the technicality. It was like hearing some foreign language and trying to catch up at-least few words that might have been said in English.\r\nFinally the meeting got over and everyone looked satisfied including customer. Everyone had a good & relaxing time that evening. We hit the best restaurant in that town and I happened to get familiar with many of the Ericsson Staff in person. Regardless of individual’s positions within the Organization, we all were just enjoying ourselves gossiping around. Many of us including myself flew next morning back to their home destinations.\r\n\r\nThis was the event which thrilled me, excited me, inspired me in many which ways. I started thinking myself, If I am satisfied with my current work profile and started comparing it with what happened in Bangkok. I made my decision and started working towards it. I got support and I am now living that moment each day of my life and trying to do more about it.\r\n\r\nNow coming back on the /// values, Have I ever served it? Thinking about it, I am','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,29,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 04:27:42','Pending'),('EMUKPOU','poushali.mukherjee@ericsson.com','Kolkata','EAMPARU','BUGS GSI GITS Application Devlopment',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-05 07:09:31','Pending'),('ERADUTT','rajesh.dutta@ericsson.com','KOLKATA','EABIBIS','BUGS GSI GITS Tools',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,31,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-05 07:13:4