ll, don\'t lie to yourself. The man who lies to himself and listens to his own lie comes to a point that he cannot distinguish the truth within him, or around him, and so loses all respect for himself and for others. And having no respect he ceases to love.','The brick walls are there for a reason. The brick walls are not there to keep us out. The brick walls are there to give us a chance to show how badly we want something. Because the brick walls are there to stop the people who don’t want it badly enough. They’re there to stop the other people. All of old. Nothing else ever. Ever tried. Ever failed. No matter. Try again. Fail again. Fail better.You never know what\'s around the corner. It could be everything. Or it could be nothing. You keep putting one foot in front of the other, and then one day you look back and you\'ve climbed a mountain.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',39,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-06 05:26:33','Pending'),('EBISJAI','bishakha.jain@ericsson.com','Kolkata','ESRSANT','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn Serv Appln CA1','','','','Narendra Modi - Prime Minister of India “I am a very optimistic man and only an optimistic man can bring optimism in the country.\" \r\nAny write up on Narendra Modi is at a risk of being written in superlatives. Either you love him or hate him. He forces you to take a stand. He polarizes. Tea vendor to PM, his story is stuff of dreams. He started attending RSS sessions when he was 8 years old. The philosophy of this organization is imprinted on everything Modi does or doesn’t. He pursued an itinerant life travelling from ashram to ashram, leaving behind his child bride Jashodaben. He joined RSS once again & found time to earn his Masters in Political Science. Modi went into hiding disguised as a Sikh when RSS was banned in the Emergency years 1975-77. He was made the general secretary of the Gujarat Lok Sangharsh Samiti. During this period he wrote a book titled Sangharsh ma Gujarat (Gujarat\'s struggle). Modi rose to prominence after organising Murli Manohar Joshi\'s Kanyakumari-Srinagar Ekta yatra in 1991.In 1988, Modi was elected as organising secretary of BJP\'s Gujarat unit. Modi declined an offer to be Gujarat CM Keshubhai Patel\'s deputy chief minister, informing Advani and Vajpayee that he was going to be fully responsible for Gujarat or not at all, and on 7 October 2001, Modi was appointed the Chief Minister of Gujarat, when Keshubhai fell ill. As Chief Minister, Modi\'s ideas of governance revolved around privatisation & small government. Then in 2002 the Gujarat riots happened, where 2000 lives were lost. Human Rights organizations world over held Modi responsible. Despite these allegations he became CM 3 more times till he resigned to become India’s PM in 2014. All parties fought tooth and nail in the 2014 elections, but all speeches were on just one issue, to vote or not vote for Narendra Modi. India and world now watches expectedly if Modi is able to create an India model, the way he created the much debated Gujarat model of development and governance.This is the real idea of Professionalism,Perseverence and Respect  for me,Modi has been successful in portraying a rare constellation of abilities by dint of these three values.','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,40,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-06 05:20:48','Pending'),('ERICPRI','richa.priya@ericsson.com','Kolkata','ESRSANT','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn Serv Appln CA1','A specific style of behaviour, abilities and conduct of an individual in an organisation defines the professionalism of the person. Every workplace may have different views and policies on the level of professionalism expected from the employees. It varies with different industries and depends on the size of the organisation. A small organisation may have more personal rapport with its employees than a big company where rules and policies dominate the game. However, some unwritten rules are universally accepted in most companies which include 