e with different teams as well as different clients and   the way people communicated with each other, respected each other’s work, attitude of people, along with polite behavior were truly professional.  Each and every one was performing their tasks with genuine earnest and honesty. Each and every one I have worked with has always lived up to their commitments. My manager and my colleagues have always been polite in speech and body language, always respected each other. They have always valued the time and effort spent by me and has always encouraged to keep up the good work.\r\nThis professional  environment in turn has ensured good performance by me, motivated me, and has ensure justice and fairness for everyone’s efforts along with good team spirit.\r\n','Employee engagement depends upon the extent to which individuals respect their organization and its leadership, and feel respected.\r\nI was assigned on a project which required travel and work from different location and  totally different role from what I had done earlier. I had to constantly communicate with clients initially it was a bit difficult but as frequent communication started to happen a relationship based on professionalism and respect was formed.  Whenever I was appreciated by the client my manager also used to appreciate my work. He used to call me and motivate me in keep on doing the good work. Everyone is looking to be recognized and respected for their individual contribution and I always received it from my manager and colleagues.  I can always express my ideas and suggestions freely and discuss with my manager and he also provide his input regarding those. Because of all this I feel Respected, Motivated, and that my skills and contribution are recognized and valued. ','After completion of my master’s degree I was not able to get job through campus interviews my job hunt started from the day I received my master’s degree.To make this worse the impact of global recession was clearly seen on Indian IT industry which resulted in less job openings.Till now already 2 months had passed and still no job.Luckily one day I received an interview call from one of the companies in which I had sent my resume earlier.I got rejected due to lack of technical exposure.This happened 3-4 times I was very frustrated as already 5 months has passed and still no job.But I was determined to get one and keep on trying. Suddenly one day I received an Interview call from an MNC regarding openings as fresher interns and will be a temporary position for 6 months.I started working and 1 week before my internship completion I was offered a permanent position in the organization because of my hard work and perseverance.It does not matter how slowly you go so long as you do not stop.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',339,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-14 08:38:00','Pending'),('EAMSAXE','amit.kumar.saxena@ericsson.com','Noida','EPALSUA','BUGS GSI Resource & Bench Mgmt',NULL,NULL,'Well, this takes me back to the Q4 of 2014 where I was doing my day to day transactions and I got a call from my manager that I have been identified for a very critical project on global level, feeling proud and timid at the same time, \r\nI realized that, will have to wear multiple hats for managing my existing and new assignments proficiently . Accepting the challenges & risks of the move, greeted this change with a lot of enthu.\r\n                                                                                 Learning & sharing best practices of different functions and maintaining consistency with my deliveries to both the new and the existing had its own challenges. I I strongly believe that I tried living the values of E/// by being resolute & professional  despite of the changes I had to embrace with happy stake-owners & successful delivery.\r\n','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',340,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 13:41:35','Pending'),('EPYNTHO','pynadath.varun.thomas@ericsson.com','Chennai','EMOHVIJ','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn ECE CA 2','','','','Following Ericsson Core Values is not just a story for us, we do it everyday....\r\n\r\nProfessionalism\r\nMoving from the \"I am the boss - You are the slave\" culture to \"We are Peers - We are a team\" is the key aspect that we learn everyday while we follow agile scrum. We, at adaptation center is an agile empowered team. Through Scrum, the best part is - we achieve our Ericsson core values by no body forcing on us,but we follow our core values by ourselves.\r\n\r\nIn the Spring Planning meeting, all of us pick up the tasks that we see we can fulfill. We show \"Professionalism\" by ensuring that we pick up tasks that we can complete in the sprint - no less, no more. When we don\'t have a boss to load us with tasks that we cannot complete, we show utmost \"Professionalism\" by doing self-justification in picking up the tasks.\r\nWhen we finish the tasks earlier and pick tasks from the \"Corner of Hope\", we cannot set another example of being \"Professional\".\r\n\r\nPerseverance\r\nOnce we pick the tasks in Sprint, it becomes our commitment to finish the tasks by the end of the sprint. We went through a hundred times where we got stuck with issues. We always have a motto - Keep Trying. When we couldn\'t find a solution for a long time, we go out for a coffee or a round of table tennis and the moment we are back, we may resolve it in a minute. But we never give up. We stared our project before one and half years and we never had a slip of delivery timeline - all sprints delivered as promised and all releases on time. The key is Perseverance.\r\n\r\nRespect\r\nWe have globally diversified team and work in different timezones .We meet for the daily scrum meetings and respect everybody in the team by being in the meeting on time. Everybody speaks his part with in a short period and everyone in team respect each other\'s opinions. We respect the roles each of us play in team. ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,341,'ESUJSIH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 07:38:37','Pending'),('ESHANVI','vijay.shanmugam@ericsson.com','Chennai','EKATHRA','BUGS GSI IP & Core-UDM','Professionalism is all about Being helpful to others, and do more than solely what\'s our defined job to make Customer happy. If we do so to make others happy, it automatically shapes us as an Energetic Professional. Ericsson creating an opportunity to unite with team to make the situation even better to bring all the employees as a Professional.\r\nI have personal experience while I visited PNG, where colleagues from different countries were helping each other whatever the situation to make the project a successful one.','A respectful work environment will always reduces the potential for conflict. In turn, this creates a more productive environment for the employer and a friendlier place for employees to work. Having respect for our colleagues earns you respect in return and creates an atmosphere where collaboration, trust and teamwork are valued.\r\nIt was the time I was new to Ericsson, where people are very kind enough to behave smart and the respect we created within and outside the team was a perfect one. Every company cannot able to create this and Ericsson did!!!','Its all about the hardwork to achieve the things on the right way.\r\nWe had an issue in the network and did some findings and highlighted the third party vendor about the same. They were not convinced. But the deep analysis we did for that issue involving all the teams to make them understand that the issue is at their end was awesome. After the everybody including customer was happy on us. Its like we can just highlight issue to them and can do our job. But for getting a resolution we need to get the things done by involving all. Ericsson allowing the employees to make this situation happen.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',342,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 04:59:59','Pending'),('ESWEKUM','sweta.kumari@ericsson.com','Noida','EANJSIL','BUGS GSI SDT R&D DU India NIM2',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'EANJSIL/ESWEKUM_Res_1676893298.avi','\"RESPECT for those who DESERVE it not for those who DEMAND it.\"',NULL,NULL,'','',343,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 10:46:43','Pending'),('EYKARTH','karthik.yerradoddi@ericsson.com','Chennai','EGOPMAT','BUGS GSI OSS CM-RNAM Pool-OM5','','','',NULL,'','','','','','','EGOPMAT/EYKARTH_All_824212130.mp4','With ordinary talent and extraordinary perseverance , everything is achievable',344,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:29:09','Pending'),('EREKSAM','rekha.prabhu.priya.samuel@ericsson.com','Chennai','EGEEMAT','BUGS GSI SI & M&A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,345,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 10:57:17','Pending'),('EDAPRAT','Pratyush.Das@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EPALSUA','BUGS GSI Resource & Bench Mgmt',NULL,NULL,'I joined Ericsson in Nov 2014 in CSI ADM, taken the role of Resource Manager in Charging Space .It\'s too  dynamic and challenging.Initially It was blank for me to understand the cause of noises coming from different region on staffing  issue. Getting my nerve to know the root causes of these challenges.I connected on regular basis with the stake holders. Excellent team support and business support with Engagement Team and Line Manager  in doing the staffing solution and sticking to a progressive plan. And on just a day after completion probation period I have been recognized for the the Power Award : Q1, 2015 .It was a wonder experience and achievement.No matter how satisfying work might be, it would be a mistake to rely on our work as our only means of satisfaction in life.there is evidence that happy people have a more balanced life, You will succeed if you persevere, and you will find a joy in overcoming obstacles.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',346,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 12:47:38','Pending'),('EYCCFGN','archana.m@ericsson.com','Chennai','EANVSIA','BUGS GSI BSS EMA-CADE Adaptn 3','','','','                                                                                \"Values Unearthing who we are\"\r\n\r\nHi friends I am Archana I have joined Ericsson few months before. I would like to share my experience. When I have joined here really am surprised how everyone in Ericsson are  living with core values , But now I can proudly say that am also living with Ericsson values. When you\'re surrounded by people who share a commitment around a common purpose, anything is possible. Since am new to the EMA product I have undergone training and it was a fantastic experience how they respect my views. Initially they started with the theoretical training later on it ended up with OJT. While I am doing my OJT training ,I had to have many discussions with my teammates.teammates. Eventhough they are very busy in their scheduled tasks, gave time to me and encouraged me .It was really admirable and helped me in completing my OJT successfully  which resulted in getting my first assignment soon. I got my first project Turkcell with less duration of time , It was my first challenging task and I have completed successfully with SSAT 100%. By Perseverance everything reaches its target .','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,347,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 09:33:50','Pending'),('ESARCHY','sanjay.kumar.c.chowdhury@ericsson.com','Kolkata','ENARVAL','BUGS GSI Service Enablmnt& Applc Unit 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,348,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 11:50:55','Pending'),('ESUPDUA','supratim.duarah@ericsson.com','Bangalore','ESHVIRE','BUGS GSI SI & OSS & Fulfillment',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'ESHVIRE/ESUPDUA_Res_1423223436.mp4','Respect : Involve Team members in Project Decision and innovative ideas',NULL,NULL,'','',349,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 12:00:07','Pending'),('QJAINIK','nikhil.jaitly@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ESONABH','BUGS GSI EMA 2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,350,'EAADMAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 12:12:09','Pending'),('EADEGIW','senthil.kumar.d.s@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3','','','','I have been around many well-respected man or woman . I used to think being Manager/teacher/Politician/scientist made them a special kind of person, but I realize that the most special thing about them was not their career, but the way they persevered.The mantel of respect always falls on those who consistently do their duty.Here is my short story which helps us understand how perseverance can help you in difficult situation.I was perform a activity of loadbalancing for 1 million subcriber from one sdp to another and I have taken complete network outage for this activity.Activity was going very smoothly until we were about to load the subcribers in the destination SDP ,I executed  the script  which loads the subscriber in the destination SDP it was around 2 AM and I have downtime only till 6 AM  in the morning thats when the script failed its execution stating with an error one of configuration dump file is missing. I tried to pull the dump again from source and tried to load it now again it gives same error.\r\n\r\nSometimes we are about to achieve our goals, but give up through lack of perseverance and patience.But I didn\'t give up I have called one my collegue for this help it was around 3 am . I  asked me create file with the name of the missing file and asked me build the dump again . Again I executed the script it throwed error. now it was 3.45 am .Now I thought about  giving up and roll back the activity but this will lead huge amount of customer escalation and credibility and the trust, which are very important values, will be lost. But my friend asked me keep it simple go by the log generated for the script execution .Then we identified the dump are getting extracted in a temporary path so we decided to place this file that temporary path.But again we the script got failed . Then we identifed that the temporary path keeps changing everytime we execute the script.So I was ready to place this immediately as soon as the script creates the temporary path. This time the script got executed successfully and I was able to complete my activity on time.So Perseverance is the drive that keeps us going even the the midst of severe trials.We all know that slow and steady wins the race, but sometimes we need a little extra encouragement to keep us going like the one i got from my friend.\r\n\r\nhere I have expressed my secret success. Are you ready to share your secret of success here is the chance \r\nhttp://eriteamtracker.egi.ericsson.com/EricssonValues/login.php','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,351,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 12:18:06','Pending'),('EFIJMOB','satheesh.m.k@ericsson.com','Chennai','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3','','','','I am speaking about my secret of success, sitting from the place from where I am. People may ask if success changes one, overnight I am just doing my job and I worked way too hard to get here.\r\nI have started my career as a support engineer to the present post of Senior Solution Integrator in an innovative company like ERICSSON.\r\nWhen I was inducted into ERICSSON and posted at Kolkata, the company has dedicated upon me certain assignments. After witnessing my hard work and sincerity in completing the work with pin point accuracy. The company has entrusted me with additional and more complex assignments.\r\n  \r\nMoreover I am proud to say that the company in recognition of my dedicated work with acute professionalism has rewarded with \"Rock star award\".\r\nProfessionalism could not be attained immediately only hard work combined with perseverance could make one professional.\r\n\r\nHowever as in other sectors the problem of skill gap does exit. There is a dearth of talent in niche areas such as Configura