thin the given time-lines. We had a meet and decided to fight , stick together and prove our mettle . We slowly started to  catch up with the pace, put our efforts tirelessly regardless of day or night , extended our working hours to overlap the time-zone, shared our expertise to get acquainted to changing technology and delivered the first sprint. For the subsequent sprint\'s it became a routine for us.\r\n     On the peak of the extent,an accident prevented me for a month and still the remaining members rocked the project towards completion. As a team we put customer first and made ourselves accountable and trusted each other with enormous courage and passion to deliver.It was a proud moment for us when we received the Fast and Flawless award for that Quarter and though i lead that project ,i am proud to say that i belong to that team full of Ericsson DNA.','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,401,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:57:26','Pending'),('EKALEES','n.kaleeswaran@ericsson.com','Chennai','EMOHVIJ','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn ECE CA 2','','','','Professionalism, Respect and Perseverance.   A person can show respect without perseverance and there can be perseverance without respect. But there cannot be professionalism without respect and perseverance. Actually speaking professionalism encompasses respect,perseverance and many more addditional qualities like being punctual,supporting team incase of distress etc. Atleast this is how my perception is towards the 3 coined terms of Ericsson\r\n\r\n	Having discussed what is professionalism its time to say with immense pride that Ericsson exhibits or to say that it even showcases professionalism.There 	 were many instances where I experienced it personally. I would like to quote one incident where I had worked for RNAM SDG project\r\n	\r\n	Due to one or more untold and unexplainable reasons the project had landed in critical state. Not a single day would pass by without bug fixes and code release. Everyone were working day-in,day-out and even during the weekends to make the project stabilize. Nevertheless the project could not be stabilized in not less than 2 months. At this time of criticality even if the managers also had lost the hope in us, it surely would have made the situation worse.\r\n	\r\n	But the managers have showcased high level of professionalism that made us comfortable. There wasnt even one harsh mail nor a single war room meeting during the 2 month period that helped us to contribute our best. To our surprise we were even compensated with allowances and comp-offs.This situation which when dealt with normal human emotions would have not only spoiled the project but also our hope in Ericsson. This is where i confirmed once again that the act of professionalism never lets you down','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,402,'EAADMAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 10:45:39','Pending'),('EFIJJNE','asha.s@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EGANVAI','BUGS GSI OSS Adaptation','','','','                                                                                                                 The Pursuit of Values \r\nI have been in Ericsson exactly for 5 months and 10 days .\r\nLike in the film  \' The Pursuit of Happyness ,\'  i am dividing these days into 3 periods .\r\n\r\nThe first month : The period of Respect\r\n \r\nThe first month ,my training period is where is saw  the magic of the value respect . \r\nI was one among the 21 GETs ,who where from different states ,\r\ndifferent colleges with different talents. But we interacted with each other through the medium of respect .\r\nSharing ,collaborating and implementing ideas of 21 brains seems not to be pragmatic ,but we achieved it .\r\nWe were free to tell our ideas and eager to listen others.The happiness we got through being kind ,polite and acknowledged\r\nwere immense. In this period i learned an important fact of my life ,\"Treat others \' not \' how you want to be treated but\r\n how they wanted to be treated.\"\r\n\r\nThe Second   and Third month  :The period of Professionalism \r\n\r\nThis was the initial transition period of an unconfined college graduate to a professional. \"Be an example for others\",\r\n\"Share your knowledge\",\"Learn from your mistakes\",these are the 3 mantras our manager told us on our first meeting to be a\r\n conscientious professional.The spark he shared with us ignited our minds.I started with the baby steps of these 3 mantras of\r\n professionalism . The discipline ,puntuality and hardworking were no more an options \r\nfor me .It became part of my life. It reflected in my personal life too. I didnt know small small things \r\nlike going somewhere in time ,not to skip the deadlines and keeping order and record of everything can make my life\r\n these simpler.\r\n\r\nFourth to present : The period of Perseverance \r\n\r\nEveryone will get a chance to show their perseverance , now its time for me .As a fresher with lot of expectations ,\r\nthis period is very crucial for me.My manager told me you can make mistakes ,but i made blunders!!\r\nThe meetings which i didnt understand a word ,the situations where i felt a fish in a sea of whales.But i know this period is\r\n just going to be an emotional and inspiring  chapter of my life .I need to be focussed , energetic and passionate .\r\nI have to do both smart and hard work .To be an example i need to be curious like a toddler ,genius like Einstein ,\r\n trustworthy like Tendulkar and stronger like superman .\r\n\r\nHolding these values in one hand i am moving towards it .Because at the end i need to achieve the period of happiness. :)  ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,403,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-14 10:34:42','Pending'),('EGUPBIK','bikash.kumar.gupta@ericsson.com','Kolkata','EGAUTDH','BUGS GSI Sprint PM',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,404,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-14 09:37:17','Pending'),('EMAJPRN','manoj.pradhan@ericsson.com','K