 Incident Manager explained me the problem and told me that the Digicel customer is facing critical problem with OneFM and not able to monitor some specific alarms and some alarms showing in OneFM WbeGUI after delay 7minutes from SO-EM EMS. He asked me to join Bridge and Lync session to resolve the issue immediately. I listened to the problem, told him about my situation. It was not possible for me to make myself available online at that moment. I gave alternative solution to Incident Manager till the time myself available online. Incident manager agreed with the solution and respected my opinion. This made me bit relaxed to attend the function.  I reached my house at 10.30PM after attending the family function. In hurry, I switched on my LAPTOP and joined the telephone Bridge. Consolidated the data from Operations team, GNOC team and Back Office team and started my investigation on production system by collecting various logfiles, packet captures etc. Then I have requested the information from back office team over call and Lync session. It was bit hard to get the information from SO-EM system as admin was not available onsite. Incident Manager has put all his effort to get the SO-EM Admin resource to get me the required information. After log waiting, I got the required alarm information from EMS Admin. I verified all OneFM details with SO-EM alarm dump shared by administrator. My luck, I found very important information in the SO-EM log file, it confirmed me that the Event time in alarm was delayed by 7 minutes in EMS Element Management System itself and some alarms were not sending proper alarm details. it was 6.00AM IST, sun was just raising and birds were waking up with their melodious sound. On Bridge Incident Manager requested the SO-EM admin to confirm on the issue at SO-EM end. Admin verified from his side and confirmed that the issue is at EMS end. EMS server time was configured with 7 minutes delay and that was causing this problem. And some transmission nodes were running with very old software which was causing missing information in the alarm.  Then I have explained the whole story to GNOC with proofs like logfiles and screenshots. GNOC got convinced and agreed to make the Ticket status from critical to RESOLVED. Finally the issue got resolved with activity assigned to EMS Admin to resolve the issue at SO-EM end. By now, it was 7.00AM Indian time. I got one mail from Incident Manager \"Thanks to Ramesh  for your wonderful patience to explain everything to everyone\". With his true story, I have experienced all core values of Ericsson Professionalism, Respect and Perseverance. proud to be part of Ericsson family.','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,458,'ESUJSIH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-16 15:57:52','Pending'),('ENPSSTT','chandrika.sharma@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EPRVMAR','BUGS GSI CD MCOM 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,459,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 10:35:16','Pending'),('EKOPRTF','thangaraj.g.g@ericsson.com','Chennai','ESRISET','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn TV CA 2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,460,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 10:38:06','Pending'),('EVAISRS','vaishnavi.devi.r.s@ericsson.com','BANGALORE','ESUNAGG','BUGS GSI OSS OSS-RC Adaptation','','','','To start our career in Ericsson is like a dream come true for me.I am lucky enough to get the oppurtunity to start my career in Ericsson.Got the chance to interact with different people ,different cultures,different view points,different technical backgrounds.Ericsson brought us together to work as a team.The tremendous support from our team helped us to cope up with the corporate world.\r\nAlso the bonding strengthened when we came to know each other very well through Confluence,OBT..Looking forward for more years ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,461,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 10:53:29','Pending'),('ESINGRI','rishikesh.singh@ericsson.com','Noida','EN