ndness.I will listen to what others say before expressing my viewpoint. I will Use people’s ideas to change or improve work whenever required. ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,470,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:13:20','Pending'),('ERATSAI','rattan.saini@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EKUMNIL','BUGS GSC EMM 4','In March 2014, I got  allocated to KSA STC project. I had no idea what this project was all about and what is the situation in the project. Within few days I had a pile of documents to go through. When I arrived on-site, situation was raining fire. I had to quickly analyze the LLD and solution which I did in a day. And during my analysis I found that there were some limitations related to ASN data structure which was restricting us to achieve the desired output. I jumped deep down into it and did all brainstorming in order to come up with a solution. And finally came up with a solution which was to make small changes in the output format. Customer was not agreeing to it but we handled the situation in a very professional way, and after showing a real life scenario of the situation customer was able to understand the situation and then after multiple discussions, finally the customer agreed to use the solution which I was proposing. Customer was satisfied and praised my effort.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',471,'ESUJSIH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 13:17:49','Pending'),('EROHABA','rohan.bajaj@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EANVSIA','BUGS GSI BSS EMA-CADE Adaptn 3','','','','CS-SDP & VS Data Migration Tool Development Vodafone India In RINA Region:\r\n\r\nI would like to share the story of CS-SDP & VS Data Migration Tool Development Vodafone India In RINA Region. This Project already had very high expectations from DM Tool Developers as this migration was very first in the 5 circle project and all from top to bottom had eyes on this migration. Also as we all know RINA as region also have their challenges , the cherry on the top  was increased complexities .Then it was realized that Data migration tool development has to be done for a new and complex implementation of MASTER-SLAVE model of SDP’s in Charging system.  This was never encountered by any Solution Architect not any DM tool developer in Past . Challenge was too High and steep with timeline pressure .\r\n\r\nHumor: Target  almost looked like a Gabbar of Indian cinema’s blockbuster Sholay. Then came our 2 Heroes  Jay and Viru alias Hari (\'G Hari Kumar Gupta and Rajani(RajaniKant Nirala) of Data Migration Tool Development came in rescue of this Project for myself (Rohan Bajaj) as Thakur alias of this project . And both of them worked day and night to complete this project and managed to bring down Gabbar  and successfully delivered the project \r\n\r\nAs a result Successful Data Migration of 6.4M subscriber in SDP and 32M vouchers in VS for Vodafone India tool place in Q12015. The Subscriber tool developed by Data Migration Tool developers was a as role model for future Data Migration projects. This DM tool development consisted of very new and complex implementations of MASTER-SLAVE models of SDP in Charging system. Tool development was so optimized that it took 45 min from receiving the file until creating the final report. Everyone shown very high level of professionalism  and respected the Timelines for the project and given 101 % in this development without any complaints .Due to this design this should scale very well as we move to larger circles and we are thinking the 25M subscriber Migration should be completed under 90 min.\r\n\r\nThis is our Story of DM Tool Development in Vodafone India:\r\n\r\nRegards \r\nRohan Bajaj, G Hari Kumar Gupta, RajaniKant Nirala\r\n','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,472,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 13:51:42','Pending'),('EQTUACK','r.jaiganesh@ericsson.com','Chennai','ERSRDHE','BUGS GSI CS CCN 1','','','','Professionalism :It is not the job you do but it’s How you do  the job. I worked for Zain Kuwait CBiO Ph1 Project where I have delivered 7 OCC Servers efficiently without any escalations. I had customer interactions  to understand their operational issues and solved it on time with the sense of accountability. I faced lot of challenges during UAT and handled that situations with the technical expertise &  persistence . I organized interactive sessions with the customer to  explain the working of OCC server and clarified the queries  with right attitude. I coordinated with third party vendors and integrated their interfaces with our OCC servers which led to the great satisfaction of the Customer. I have followed the Ericsson \r\nRespect:    \r\nEricsson has given me the opportunity to explore various cultures and lifestyle of people from different countries .These experiences have taught me to work in a cross-cultural team where we worked with sense of respect for each other’s customs .we all worked as a team where everyone’s ideas and suggestions are considered and valid ideas are appreciated and accepted by the team. Through the act of appreciation, everyone felt respected and that resulted in active participation of each and every person.\r\nPerseverance:\r\n I Supported live subscriber migration activity and work hard and spent sleepless nights  to achieve the milestone of the project. I have understood the root cause of critical issue with packet core integration  and solved the problem on time. Finally I learnt that John Quincy Adams’s words “patience and Perseverance have magical effects before which difficulties disappear and obstacles vanish” \r\n','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,473,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 17:58:11','Pending'),('ETTTAAA','arun.kumar.t@ericsson.com','Chennai','ERANANA','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA CRS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,474,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 15:55:37','Pending'),('EABTSHN','abhijit.sharan@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EKATHRA','BUGS GSI IP & Core-UDM','','','','Let me just share a small story about my journey with Ericsson. It has been 5 years since I have been a part of the Ericsson family and every bit of my duration of stay in this organization has helped me build upon the three values, rather the three pillars of Ericsson\'s success story. Professionalism, Respect and Perseverance... these are not mere words, we the employees of Ericsson, live by these values and I feel it in all my actions.\r\n\r\nProfessionalism, which means putting customer first in any scenario, is a core value practiced at each location and instance. Delivering an assignment is not just enough in terms of professionalism, there needs to be more. Our customers need to be the apostles or band ambassadors for our service quality to the rest of the world. Ericsson had always been a leader in terms of delivering customer excellence in all its services. Our key objective is to provide not only customer satisfaction but customer delight. This is professionalism redefined!\r\n\r\nRespect, the value which enables Ericsson employees to innovate and make decisions faster, has definitely helped me learn and grow in my career graph. I have not only gained respect from my colleagues and customers but also learned and practiced the value myself. This grooms me as both an individual as well as professional.\r\nI started working with Ericsson in 2010, and was with D&P UPE. Then, I moved from EIL to EGI. For this, my manager and the entire team supported me in my decision and their respect and confidence helped me to take the next step in my career. I have recently moved to CSI, this is an innovative step and a learning process for me where I am molding my career, innovating and generating solution for my customers in every assignment that I am taking up. All thanks to my Eric family.\r\n\r\nThe third pillar of success for Ericsson and me as an employee is Perseverance. Constant improvement and no Complacence, is the key to growth and improving standards of work. I as an employee of Ericsson, feel that in spite of all the technical challenges which prop up every now and then, I and my team have never given up in terms of efforts and constant improvement in terms of our service quality. I have always tried to walk an extra mile and achieve what is better than the best for our clients. I do not believe in being complacent, as it stagnates your thought process and kills your growth and quest for knowledge. \r\n\r\nIt is not only my personal experiences which make me say that the three values are pillars of success for Ericsson, I see the success story of every leader at Ericsson as a saga based on these three values. It is instilled in the regular activities of all the employees of Ericsson. This is helping the organization achieve greater heights with each passing day. I would like to further state that these values not only make Ericsson stand out in the huge gamut of service sector organizations, but if imbibed will make an individual also stand out as a star prof','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,475,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 19:42:52','Pending'),('EPRUVXA','arun.kumar.s@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EBPBPBP','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 5','In Ericsson professional workplace behavior plays a vital role in long-term success of a business. Our interactions and relationships with customers are of vital importance to ensure that company goals and objectives are met. Ericsson professional work place attitude and appearance allows our employees to take pride in their work and improve worker performance. Our Managers who behave professionally an appropriate example by encouraging our people to conduct us in a manner that supports company-wide success. Business environment in which our employees dress and operate professionally is more conducive for success.','In Ericsson professionalism in business establishes respect for authority figures, clients and co-workers. We us a team Maintaining a professional demeanor limits gossip and inappropriate personal conversations that could be considered disrespectful. Keeping a professional attitude with clients who behave inappropriately demonstrates the level of respect an employee has for the customer and the business partnership. Our pals were very respective to each other apart from sex, age and designation.\r\n','In Ericsson Perseverance plays an important role among our employees. This indeed makes our pals to work towards the success. Our employees had set the quote \"Never, never, never give in\" in their minds and working hard to grow themselves as well for the growth of our reputed company.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',476,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-15 20:49:25','Pending'),('EHKLMOY','s.arunkumar@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EBPBPBP','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 5','','','','For me being a professional, Ericsson\'s values are nothing but the values of life. What do you think?\r\nI always calibrate my own success/achievements based on how much I have contributed towards these values; this is applicable to both my professional and personal life.\r\nI just want to share; I just want to recap my 3 years of project journey with Ericsson values, oops!! Sorry the value of life. \r\nHere you go “The Story of 100\'s\"\r\nMy journey with Ericsson started in the year 2012.\r\nRight from the start I got the opportunity to work with customers from different regions (RINA,RMEA,RASO,RMED,RSSA ) directly ,they differ by time,climate,culture,language and work nature. Few are easy to handle and some are difficult to convince. So I always set my mind flat and flexible so  it helps me to adapt/adjust for any situations.\r\nTo handle a customer first you should adhere to Ericsson values apart from this you should be confident, a good listener and talkative. Yes of course as a professional we should have these qualities by default and I strongly feel I have learned these skills from all my projects and I keep developing it. \r\nProfessionalism:\r\nProfessionalism is being punctual. When I was working for Batelco Bahrain, I use to work from customer office every day, their working time starts at 7 AM where I use to reach customer office ahead to maintain the high degree of professional punctuality and this was appreciated by customer.\r\nProfessionalism is taking responsibilities. In Mcel Mozambique, the project doesn’t have solution architect. Even though I was assigned as a SI, understanding the situation I took the SA responsibility to fulfill my project requirement to avoid delay in delivery. \r\nProfessionalism is satisfying customer commitments. Recently in Algeria in spite of being assigned for Djezzy project I have asked for emergency support to upgrade 7 CCN’ in 9 days for ooredoo. I have delivered on-time without any issue.\r\nRespect:\r\nI always prefer to stay at customer location .I have done that at all the times for customers like Batelco, Djezzy, Mcel and Airtel to hear from them all the time. Since listening to customer is the biggest respect you offer them. \r\nI always respect their timelines and wait for their unanswered emails.\r\nI always prefer to have fair relation with customer, few customers talk beyond work still I listen to make them comfortable. \r\nPerseverance:\r\nI have maintained high standard of delivery on 10 projects which I have handled so far in Ericsson which includes 5 different regions with more than 8 different customers with total of 10 consecutive 100% SSAT.  \r\nI have received appreciation directly from customers like Djezzy, Mcel, Batelco, Airtel, and GrameenPhone. And I have delivered complex projects with different scope of works.\r\nRecently I have received Fast and Flawless award for Airtel Bangladesh MBC project.  In past I have received 3 Ace and a power award.\r\nI have shown my best so far. Hope to grow beyond and achieve mor','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,477,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-16 10:12:00','Pending'),('ESAYPAY','sanjay.y.pandey@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ESUADAS','BUGS GSI ADM-Test Factory-M&A TAAS','','','','Though this story belongs to my previous project in 2014 i.e. A1 Telekom Austria where I was associated as Test Lead.\r\nIn Sept 2013, A1 (Customer) raised some concern over some of the deliverable\'s quality. Me, My team started working on that, preparing data for Upper Management to answer their questions. Defining new standards for up scaling the quality. Redefining estimation. Introducing new quality processes. And so on.\r\nOne fateful day...25th Feb 2014.\r\nSame like all days.I woke up at 5:45 AM..was getting ready to catch my Office Cab which was scheduled for 6:55AM. My phone rang...my brother in law called me up...I got tensed and worried because He never calls me in morning or even in noon time.\r\nI picked up the phone, before I could say Hello!!! I heard his voice \"Jija Ji (Me) Please Save Papa...He has got heart attack.\" He was crying loud.\" I could hear the voice of my Wife, She also was crying loud (that time She was expecting and went Varanasi to meet her Father and Bother.\r\nI could not say anything...i become numb because it was my first experience like this.. I never handled such situation ...I was literally shivering. I tried to console them that do not worry He will be fine. He disconnected the phone. I booked the next available flight immediately which was at 11:30. Since critical deliveries were planned I had to manage my work as well, I opened my Laptop and first mail I sent to my Manager, stating him the situation. I messaged to my whole team that I won’t be able to come to office. I prepared the list of task to be carried out for next 1 week and shared with the team. I mailed each and every information to my backup Sheetu with each and every minor detail. \r\nAt 7:43 AM, I got a call from my Father that my Father in laws has passed away. I went in shock...but that time only I understood that I had to manage the things in Varanasi. I took my scheduled flight, reached Varanasi. Arranged everything for his funeral. \r\n2 Days Gone...My bother in law asked if I could stay there till his father\'s 13hi and look after the business ( I had no idea about his business) and Home. I could not say no. But my work at office...how that would be done!!! So I called my Manager Sankar Ganesh and asked his permission to Stay. I promised him that delivery and other things won’t be hampered. So I had to keep my words.\r\nSo I started carrying my laptop to His Business. Started working from there like I used to do from my seat, managing all my deliverables. I spend 21 days in Varanasi, settled down everything, His business, Home &everything.  \r\nMost Importantly I could successfully deliver my Duties to which I was bound to. My project A1 Telekom Austria, with My team. Nothing was missed… We successfully delivered the release with 0 critical/high defects.\r\nRespect, Professionalism and Perseverance, I live with this, I will always live with these values. \r\nI have a huge respect for Sankar Ganesh: Sankar you are one of the best Managers/Best Mentors of my life','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,478,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-16 07:10:21','Pending'),('EJAVIPU','vipul.v.jain@ericsson.com','Noida','ESHAHHA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 4','','','','Professionalism, Respect and Perseverance - These three words are not limited to me as my work place values, they flow in blood. They are part of my DNA. Overa  career span of more than 12 years these values had helped me in every sphere of my life, be it professional or personal. ','','','','','','','ESHAHHA/EJAVIPU_All_532793550.mp4','I WORK AT ERICSSON !! NEED TO SAY MORE ?',479,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 04:07:39','Completed'),('EMAHITI','mahesh.shekhar.iti@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EVINKUP','BUGS GSI SDT R&D DU India OneFM_Auto',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,480,'EAADMAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-17 06:13:00','Pending'),('EPRNJAL','praveen.j.jaiswal@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EMATKOG','BUGS GSI ADMS & TAAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,481,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 02:35:26','Pending'),('EMAHSAU','saurabh.mahajan@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ESUADAS','BUGS GSI ADM-Test Factory-M&A TAAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,482,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 04:38:10','Pending'),('EVIVGOE','vivek.kumar.goel@ericsson.com','BANGALORE','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3','','','','True Success!-A journey of New Blood\r\n\r\nSuccess is just a relative word. I wouldn\'t just define success as to achieve, rather I would love to define success as a feeling of satisfaction, earning respect, and building of a relationship.\r\n\r\nThis story is about Bharti India -RINA Y3 project. We were a group of 12-15 engineers (recently joined CSI-ADM) who were working on their first project in E// .For many, it was the first experience with any E// product. We all were very enthusiastic to work on a project, but we very little knew that it was going to be an everest climbing task with lots of expectations, hard-work, sleepless nights and full of coordination. We started this journey together, trying to build a bonding, harvesting a culture to help each other and helping each other learn. Days moved on, weeks passed by, one after the other SDP\'s got installed , but all of a sudden, we got a push from CPM to get around 25 SDP\'s installed and made live within 30 days time (march-2015) . The CPM knew it was not an easy task, but he made us believe in ourselves and respect the customer need.\r\n\r\nFinally, We all together made E// proud in front of the customer after long tiring days and sleepless nights, sharing the work load among ourselves and made all the SDP\'s live with 5 days to spare (from the dead line).\r\n\r\nThis work was well appreciated by the customer and CPM. Each of us was happy that we could live upto our own expectations, we each could have helped E// build a reputation of Fast and Flawless delivery and most importantly demonstrate the spirit of team work together.\r\n\r\nThis is what I call success!. A true success story, where we could live upto expectations (even better it), create a culture, build a fruitfull relationship with customer and most importantly, identify our own strengths.\r\n\r\nI personally would like to wish all of my team members best of luck and would really love to work with them in future.','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,483,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:46:15','Pending'),('ESMAMNK','mayank.a.sharma@ericsson.com','BANGALORE','EKMNPQS','BUGS GSI ADM&TAAS&TAAS3','','','','Getting first professional job feels like a big leap into the real world. First day at a new job can be overwhelming and exhausting. We are unclear about expectations big and small, haven\'t yet figured out the office pecking order, and don\'t even know where the kitchen is and not to mention how to use the coffee machine. Here is a short story of a fresher whose negativity is about to turn into a whole new experience, a story that is an end to weak thinking of first day. It’s a beginning of a new era of Joy, Happiness, Professionalism and RESPECT.  \r\nWhere respect is an unspoken way of communication; which builds unshaken and strong relationship and being professional helps to resolve the differences on a one to one basis, no matter how irrational someone makes.\r\nI am ERICSSON. We are one.\r\n','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,484,'ESUJSIH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 08:46:09','Pending'),('ERUVVXD','disha.s@ericsson.com','Gurgaon','EKUMNIL','BUGS GSC EMM 4',NULL,NULL,'Perseverance isn\'t limited to the early stage of a person\'s career. It\'s a drive that keeps us going even in the midst of severe trials. Perseverance is all about trying harder and harder to achieve your goals. This can be done only when you are highly focused on what you want to be. Same thing happened with me when I was applying for jobs, there was a time when I got rejected by many companies.But instead of giving up I tried harder and gone for another with more preserved nature and got selected at end and now I\'m a part of Ericsson.\r\n                                  Trying hard to do thingswell is much more satisfying than doing them just to an ordinary standard.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',485,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:08:32','Pending'),('ESUNALO','Sunakshi.Longani@ericsson.com','Gurgaon','ESONABH','BUGS GSI EMA 2',NULL,NULL,'\"Never quit, never give up, never lose your faith! ITS THE ONE REASON YOU WALK THIS EARTH.\" Story of  MY REBIRTH .I got to know the importance of life when I met with a major accident. That was the time when there was no hope of my survival. During that time I lost all the hope to live life.I had multiple fractures in legs n many more injuries but I had spirit to live and support of my family and friends.  I gathered strength to live life in a different way and search for the happiness. I decided NOT TO GIVE UP .Though I was not having the support of my legs and some body parts that time but I was having perseverance within myself and the support of my near and dear ones. I recovered from that soon and from past few years after that horrible day of my life I am living the life with full determination and dedication. Now I am enjoying the different challenges of life. Its rightly said \" Life is not easy for any of us. We must have perseverance and above all confidence in ourselves.\"','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',486,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:41:55','Pending'),('EBCFFGX','Yashaswi@ericsson.com','Noida','EILBRIJ','BUGS GSI RAN-3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,487,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 06:09:57','Pending'),('EASWINI','aswini.v@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EBARAJA','BUGS GSI Adaptation Delv Ofc','','','','Respect - Everyone deserves to be treated good - Treat others as how you would like to be treated\r\nProfessionalism - Keep Calm, Make Situation Right  - Take Responsibility & Listen Actively\r\nPerseverance  - Continued Effort Despite Difficulty  - Stubbornness with a purpose will yield success\r\n\r\nStay tuned to Ericsson Values to grow and succeed. \r\n','','','','','','','EBARAJA/EASWINI_All_122212051.mp4','A day @ ericsson',488,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 08:23:07','Completed'),('ECHAJAS','jasmine.chana@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ERAMBPA','BUGS GSI OSS Engagement Cluster','','','','Here are my thoughts on Ericsson’s core values of Respect, Perseverance and Professionalism. Well, I believe, these are not only ‘Ericsson’s’ core values, these are the building blocks of a successful, yet humble human being. \r\nRespect is the very essence of our personality that’s imbibed in us right from our birth and matures as we grow up. It’s not only how we handle our customers or managers in office or elders at home, it’s also how we handle and groom our team at office and kids at home. Respect is something that is mutual- It’s not a one way street. There’s an age old saying- ‘You have to earn respect’.  Well I would like to differ on that. Respect is something people surrounding you will themselves sense -You don’t have to do anything special to ‘earn’ it. \r\nIt’s simple- the moment you see your ideal colleague fighting, shouting and abusing in middle of the road – you lose all the respect you had for him, gathered from years of interaction. \r\nPerseverance is a CHOICE that you yourself make for your growth and success. It is something that doesn’t let you fail in life when you fail in one chapter! It is something that gets you up every morning no matter how tired you are and brings you to work. Perseverance is something that can surpass intelligence. Perseverance is an ATTITUDE that never lets you quit anything. Perseverance alone can get you ahead in life. \r\nAfter all, perseverance is something that gave is Bulb!!\r\nProfessionalism is a quality that I believe an organization inculcates in you. You learn it and you take it from others. You are not taught about this in schools, you can’t be taught this at home. It’s single and most important value that only a work culture can groom in you. Ericsson demonstrates and feeds this in you so strongly that even when you move out, you take it with you- It’s with you for life! Head of GSI inviting for a one to one discussion and assuring to keep it with himself- Well that’s Professionalism!! And that’s how it flows- top to bottom and grows- employee to employee!!\r\n','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,489,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 06:29:27','Pending'),('EKUIANU','anu.kumari@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EAMJAIS','BUGS GSI EMM 3','In one of my projects with Airtel Niger, i got a call from my CPM asking to look into an urgent issue at 12am. I logged in to the node from home and worked untill 5am in the morning until the issue was resolved. I kept in mind the value of Ericsson of being  professional and keeping customer first and help the organisation to achieve more and more each passing day. We the employees are the pillars of the company and our every deed should reflect the values of Ericsson.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',490,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 06:53:30','Pending'),('EABKMAN','abhishek.mahajan@ericsson.com','Pune','ESKPKUM','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA Billing 4','','','',NULL,'','','','','','','ESKPKUM/EABKMAN_All_192368359.wmv','Ericsson Values in our prespective',491,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:37:58','Pending'),('EZADDDE','richa@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EGOEMUK','BUGS GSI EMM 1','','','',NULL,'','','','','','','EGOEMUK/EZADDDE_All_1592930981.avi',' These values are what that define the organization and are experienced by everyone new or old'