ctly rate your success based on how persistantly you doing that job, as we heard the story of rabbit and tortoise from childhood, persiverence is the key to success offcourse our speed does catalyst job. I do implement same here at my job.\r\n\r\nPerseverance brings Respect and both together build you Proffesionally','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,498,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:19:33','Pending'),('EANUVEN','anusha.venugopal@ericsson.com','Noida','EGAUPIY','BUGS GSI BSS RINA CAC Support',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,499,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 08:32:07','Pending'),('ESURYAP','suryaprakash.k@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EBPBPBP','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 5','','','','i want to share my experience in project where Professionalism along with \r\nperseverance helped us to get the project completed on time .As a result we got great respect \r\nand appreciation from the customer.i have been assigned with the project in one of the \r\nleading telecom operator in india.\r\n\r\n	Since we are required to work on the production node all work has been planned only at\r\nnight time and this continued more than 3 months where we showed\r\nour perseverance to get the task completed on time. Also the hardware is new and this \r\nis the first time we are implmenting the same  we got so many new obstacles which stood\r\nas a barrier to the completion,but as team with great respect to work and perseverance we managed \r\nto complete the work on time.\r\n\r\nSo as a result of following our core values we got a best result of customer satisfation and a great appreciation.','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,500,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:29:28','Pending'),('EPRMADH','praveen.madhwal@ericsson.com','Noida','EGAUPIY','BUGS GSI BSS RINA CAC Support',NULL,'Respect : More you give , More you get , I am very fortunate to be part of such a team which fosters such value among each other . In my point of view , the ability to recognize and respects individual differences is the beginning of building a successful team .if I recount one of my experience when I was working on certain problem for RINA region there I had to co-ordinate with people from different teams , At first we all were at unease welcoming everybody point of views , but gradually we all learn to be modest , be respectful to each other opinion and tried to understand and solved the problem within requested time line. we received acknowledgement and appreciation from client and management as well. I draw a lesson out of this that one don\'t care how much you know , unless they know how much u care.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',501,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 08:57:15','Pending'),('EZDEEEH','ankit.g.sharma@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EJAVIPU','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 4','','','',NULL,'','','','','','','EJAVIPU/EZDEEEH_All_1141295795.avi','Respect to be backbone of Business solution',502,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 08:54:39','Pending'),('EGAABHI','abhinav.g.garg@ericsson.com','Noida','EANTYAG','BUGS GSI DU & E SS1',NULL,'I am not going to share anything about me..I am going to share about Ericsson..every company dose lots of CSR initiatives.. but name any one company apart from E\\\\\\ who has Emergency Response Group formed with the help of Ericsson Employees who has voluntered themself.. today I proudly share with every one.. the RESPECT WE SHOWS NOT ONLY TOWARDS OUR CO-WORKERS ALSO TOWARD HUMANITY..be it a EBOLA CRISIS or Haiti  Earthquake...or J &K Flood or Nepal.. ERICSSON stood everywhere to supoprt at there best in everyterms.. financially or by Humanitarians or restoring the Communication quickly.. This eally make me proud to SAY I WORK WITH ERICSSON and TRY TO LIVE ERICSSON VALUES...',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',503,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:20:28','Pending'),('ESAANKU','ankur.s.saxena@ericsson.com','Noida','EANTYAG','BUGS GSI DU & E SS1','I am part of CSI ADM DU Dubai Account working in OSS Service Assurance. Last year in month of September we received a request to deliver  big and complex  Change Requests of (100 man days efforts) in same month. Unfortunately the CR was critical and delay could lead to impactful financial loss to the customer at the same time we were struggling with the resource availability in team.. \r\nUnderstanding the business criticality and the impact Me and one of my team member decided to go extra mile to support customer in their tough time. We created one automation script to configure the alarms which used to be configured manually earlier in Netboss. \r\nYou must have listened \r\n\"“Do your work with your whole heart and you will succeed – there’s so little competition.\" \r\n\r\nOur Automation script did its wonder saving 60 man days of efforts and best part was the complete delivery was defect free.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'','EANTYAG/ESAANKU_Pro_514213318.avi','Be Professional and you will be successful!!!!!',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',504,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:11:50','Pending'),('EMOADIL','mohd.adil@ericsson.com','Noida','ESUADAS','BUGS GSI ADM-Test Factory-M&A TAAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,505,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:03:02','Pending'),('EUTKJAU','utkarsh.jauhari@ericsson.com','Noida','EANTYAG','BUGS GSI DU & E SS1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,506,'EAADMAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:06:15','Pending'),('EUBCDFT','amit.kumar.c.singh@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EMATKOG','BUGS GSI ADM-Test Factory-OSS TAAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,507,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:10:16','Pending'),('ESUNMON','sunny.monga@ericsson.com','Noida','ERACSRI','BUGS GSI BSS CADE-Mob Mon Adaptation','','','','Ericsson core values; Profeesionalism, Respect & Perseverance play vital role in our day to day life. It\'s not enough to apply these only in our professional life, however it is recommended to apply these in our personal as well as professional lives. Ericsson stresses more on these values so that it may inherit in all of us after all we are the brand ambassodor of Ericsson. \r\nIf I coorelate these values with an example, I am working in support project where it is mandatory to understand the criticality of customer business either I am sleeping or running some errands or I am under the wheather, customer always comes first.\r\nDuring my tenure in Ericsson I had learned to respect towards our customers, culture and company.\r\nNotwithstanding how upset the customer is or how much pressure is there to achieve the milestone, I have to be confident and good listener who could understand the problem and able to pacify the customer by providing him the resolution within timelines.\r\nI am fortunate to be among such collegues who have never say never attitude, no matter how critical the requirement is or how tight the timelines is. \r\nFor me Perseverance in life is an essential quality if one is to realize their goals and achieve success. In my point of view, whatever endeavors we pursue, when armed with the virtue of perseverance our success is guaranteed.\r\nHave a clear step-by-step plan of how you\'re going to achieve your goal. Your plan is your roadmap to your desired destination. Simply without one you\'ll deviate.\r\nBefore you start your pursuit of a goal, make a commitment to yourself that you will work towards it for a specific period of time and won\'t give up before that time arrives. Make this period as long or as short as you want but the important thing is not to quit before the allotted time.\r\nSelf-control is a must when developing perseverance in daily life. Exercising self-control ensures you remain focused on the task or tasks in hand, and not get side-tracked and distracted.\r\nEstablish consistent daily habits. Take small steps of progress consistently everyday will mean that your efforts will compound and success will be inevitable.\r\nThe importance of perseverance in life cannot be stressed enough. To achieve any notable goal or success then you must have the stamina to stay the distance.','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,508,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:12:17','Pending'),('EDEKATK','deepak.kisan.katkar@ericsson.com','Pune','ESKPKUM','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA Billing 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,509,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:36:19','Pending'),('EAMTJOI','amit.anant.joshi@ericsson.com','PUNE','EMARSUK','BUGS GSI SI & OSS Strategic',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,510,'ESUJSIH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:37:27','Pending'),('ECJABAS','c.javeed.basha@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EBPBPBP','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,511,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 09:51:07','Pending'),('ENQSTUB','selvakumar.s@ericsson.com','Chennai','ERSRDHE','BUGS GSI CS CCN 1','A professional writer is an amateur who didn’t quit\r\n\r\nTo me Professionalism means to exhibit honesty, integrity, never compromising on their values, holding accountable for their thoughts, words and actions along with a self-discipline and self-regulation, confidentiality. \r\nProfessionalism is a frame of mind and not a paycheck. \r\n','Treat to Re-Treat or Retreat\r\n\r\nI think it’s funny that people who treat you like shit get offended when you finally do the same to them.\r\nTreat people the way that you want to be treated. Respect is earned and not given\r\nRespect your fellow human being, treat them fairly, disagree with them honestly, enjoy their friendship, explore your thoughts about one another candidly, work together for a common goal and help one another achieve it.\r\n','Stubbornness with a purpose, dedication, and a commitment\r\n\r\nPerseverance is the hard work you do after you get tired of the hard work you already did.\r\nGet committed, and get dedicated to the commitment.\r\nUncommon achievers are different, In a doubting world, they believe;In a slow world, they run;In a weeping world, they laugh;In a quitting world, they persevere.\r\nA pessimist sees the difficulty in every opportunity, an Optimist sees the Opportunity in every difficulty -	Sir Winston Churchill\r\nSometimes you just have to pick yourself Up and carry on to \"Deliver your vision, & Capture your Brand\"\r\n\r\nAt last not just to stand with blogging only, but to Persevere to carry Professionalism and Respect all along thus developing a self -value\r\nKeep your self-values to adapt and to adopt Organizational Values... For Ericsson, To Ericsson and By Ericsson\r\n','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',512,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:20:05','Pending'),('ESUBMAD','subramanian.madhanabharatam@ericsson.com','Chennai','ETINMAD','BUGS GSI CD-BSS Portfolio','','','','Professionalism Respect and Perseverance orchestrated for success:\r\n\r\nProfessionalism,Respect and Perseverance is the guiding note for an individual and for organization to attain success. These core values have to be well orchestrated. I relate these core values to an opera where the music experts and singers form together and cordinate their core vlaues to provide a dramatic music. I see bees showcasing these values while developing a beehive and maintaining it. Ants moving in line and gathering food is another classic example. These natural examples are eventually success formula. We respect the principles and start understanding how to cope up for organisation success. To me all these values goes hand in hand when we deal with our customers,society and competitors. ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,513,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 10:29:28','Pending'),('EASJOHR','ashish.johri@ericsson.com','Pune','EAVNVAR','BUGS GSI E2E Architecture Group 4','','','','Hi,\r\n\r\nWe (Ashish Johri & Rajesh Shetty) became a part of Ericsson family fairly recently and therefore consider ourselves to be still quite young :)&#61514;\r\n\r\nIt was only post our joining that we became aware of the Ericsson values of ‘Professionalism’, ‘Respect’ and ‘Perseverance’.\r\n\r\nHowever, we are glad that we don’t feel out of place in this organization and can definitely relate to ‘ALL’ and not just one of these values.  Not sure whether our friends; who recommended our candidature for this job, did so because they also identified us with any/all of these values!  \r\n\r\nAnd surprisingly, all the people we have come in contact with since our joining, have exemplified some or the other, if not all of these values. Be it the colleagues whose seats we temporarily capture and return it to them when they smilingly reclaim them (Professional), or the colleagues who help us find our way around with extracting Xerox and print outs (Respectful) or those who never tire to help us with the numerous portals/links/requisitions/etc (Perseverant)……..  and the list is still building up.\r\n\r\nSo as this family grows, we sure will seek to invite our friends and acquaintances, who also possess…….and live these values!\r\n\r\nLooking forward to happy times being a part of this family.....as it continues to grow and prosper!\r\n','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,514,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 10:25:07','Pending'),('EVISKAV','vishnu.kavithan@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,515,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 10:12:04','Pending'),('ESRPADH','srinivas.padhy@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ERUCGUP','BUGS GSI SDT R&D DU India Testing',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,516,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 10:41:03','Pending'),('ESKMASI','mohammed.asif@ericsson.com','Chennai','EDUTSAN','BUGS GSI BSS EMA-CADE Adaptn 6',NULL,NULL,'No great thing is created suddenly:\r\n\r\nI am Mohammed Asif, working as a Software Engineer in EMA-CA team from past 2 years.\r\nIt is important that we all start to think about what Perseverance means.\r\nFor me, perseverance means to keep going through a hard time without giving up and it is a great element of success.\r\n\r\nExample: If you only knock long enough and loud enough at the door, you are sure to wake up somebody.\r\n\r\nI am going to share my work experience of Zain KSA project,\r\nInitial phase our team faced major challenges like,\r\nRequirements were not documented properly, no HLD and also Visualising the End to End flow is hard.\r\n\r\nWe overcame the issues by,\r\nPartial delivery mechanism and thorough pre-analysis was great, with good assignment breakdown.\r\nGood load sharing and co-ordination among team members during dynamic requirement changes is  a key element for success.\r\n\r\nInstead of thinking to gave up(where we could have missed business), we worked hard and satisfied the custome','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',517,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:13:36','Pending'),('ERPNGOU','r.p.nagana.goud@ericsson.com','BANGALORE','ERISDAS','BUGS GSI MS Cricket QA BO','','','','                                  \r\n                                    RNAM_US_TE_Cricket_QA_BO_Ericsson_Core_Values\r\nEricsson Core Values:\r\nEricsson core values are respect, professionalism and perseverance. Core values play such an important role in our lives, being able to recognize, understand and articulate one’s own values set becomes critical in sound decision making. Additionally, the ability to identify an organization values will assist in determining an employee’s job performance and allegiance. Consequently, when an individual discovers genuine and meaningful alignment between his or her own personal values with those of his or her organization, a powerful connection is created. This connection creates numerous possibilities for both individual growth and company productivity, manifested in myriad ways.\r\nRespect:\r\nCricket is a project where we deal with E2E testing which includes BW and BI testing. In Cricket we validate ledgers and accounting details with EBS/ALE glass system. We got great opportunity to work on back end system where it involves Data Base and UNIX.  The fusion of personal values with a project expressed work ethic and resulted in the development of greater employee’s respect for the project. The need to generate employee enthusiasm and dedication to product produced or service rendered is of utmost concern and infuse passion and respect in those services delivered by individual and team work to the Cricket project. There has been a long held maxim that if an employee truly believes in the work that he or she performs for an project , that employee will be encouraged to create a necessary, safe and beneficial service or product with pride, dedication and respect to purpose. In Cricket, employees are recognized with monthly awards for innovative ideas and services delivered by individual. Our ideas, abilities and unique point of view make a tremendous contribution to the strength of our team and project. We have an environment that promotes respect and fairness for all resources and we value each other’s diversity. \r\nRepresented E/// and did exceptionally well in the CMMI SCAMPI-B assessment (July\r\n2014) and qualified for the next level i.e. SCAMPI-A assessment which is planned to be\r\nheld in August this year.\r\n90% of the team members are of JS4 and hence the YoY cost optimization is exemplary\r\nwithin CSI-ADM\r\nReceived overall satisfaction index of 5.00 (100%) (the highest ever) provided by\r\nChristopher Weber, for the period from 2014-09-04 to 2015-02-22.\r\nWe have a culture of respect and mutual trust among us which provides a very fostering environment which encourages all its employees to work whole heartedly.\r\nWe joined as GET, we were completely new to the project and were eager to learn from seniors. Team members were never felt neglected in case of issues. Received appreciation from team leaders for the work that we have delivered at each phase.\r\nContinuous utilization of 100% in last 2 years.\r\nZero release esca','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,518,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:34:46','Pending'),('ESAABDM','saranya.v@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','ESHLSIE','BUGS GSI Sprint Fac','','','','I have done knowledge sharing with my colleagues which displays value of professionalism\r\n\r\nTreating all my colleague with respect ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,519,'EAADMAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 13:24:08','Pending'),('EMIRAJE','rajeev.mittal@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ERANANA','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA CRS','','','','I have been working with Ericsson India for more than 6 years. In this journey as a part of projects I have visited various countries. I would like to share an incident during one of my visit to Cuba which showcases living the core values of Ericsson viz Professionalism, Perseverance and Respect. \r\nAs part of safety and security I register myself with the Indian Embassy whenever I visit any country and I did the same in Cuba. One day I got a call from the Indian Embassy and they contacted stating they had an issue with their Hughes Satellite internet switch at the Ambassador’s residence. Since I was registered as Engineer and working for Ericsson they were wondering if I can fix it for them. Cuba being embargo country procuring a new switch will cost money and time. \r\nI showed great Respect to their request and visited the Ambassador’s residence to understand the problem they have. To me this situation is like facing a customer and I took up the challenge in a Professional manner and asked them if they can give the switch to analyze and troubleshoot. \r\nThe local technician who had inspected the switch earlier had given a final report as this is completely damaged and cannot be rectified. \r\nWith no internet connection available readily, finding any troubleshooting references was impossible. The only way was to open the switch to check for any faulty part. Language being a constraint, with great difficulty I was able to procure a toolkit somehow from the Hotel technician. Split opened the switch with the available tools, and inspected thoroughly. It seemed one of the component in the switch was damaged and replacement might bring back the switch in running condition. \r\nTo get this part in a country where Spanish is the official language was a challenge. The Perseverance to find a solution drove me to the local shops with some help and was able to secure the required part. The part was replaced and the switch’s LED indicators starter glowing which was dead earlier. Took the switch to the Ambassador’ residence and connected it to check. It was a proud moment when the switch started working perfectly fine and Internet was getting accessed. The Ambassador was very happy with my work and considered me as part of the their family which gave me a feeling of home away from home.\r\nI approached this as if I work for Ericsson customer and I was able to live our core values of Professionalism, Perseverance & Respect to solve the problem. \r\nThe Respectable moment was when I was invited for a dinner party at the Indian Ambassador’s residence along with Ambassadors from Russian, Japanese and Mexican Embassies. I was introduced to the Dignitaries as an Ericsson employee from India working on project in cuba for telecom operator ETECSA. This made the name of Ericsson and India both Shine in the presence of an International Forum.\r\nEricsson’s core values, Professionalism, Respect & Perseverance have helped me in many situations including the one I have shared here. ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,520,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:08:27','Pending'),('EMRIBHA','mrinal.bhattacharjee@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EANVSIA','BUGS GSI BSS EMA-CADE Adaptn 3',NULL,NULL,'Hii  I am Mrinal from EMA Customer Adaptation Team, Part of CSI-ADM, EGI\r\nI would like to share my experince as an Ericsson employee. Ericsson\'s values are not only lived upto by its employees but even Customer\'s reasonates with its values. As a lead developer in Zain Bahrain\'s EMA adaptation development I had experienced that Customer respects Ericsson\'s brand and as a result its employees commands respect. But we commanded respect even from our rival vendors due to our professionalism. I met with accidents during project but thanks to the support and perseverance of Ericsson Family that I could sucessfully and flawlessly deliver it at the end.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EANVSIA/EMRIBHA_Per_628418959.mp4','Its gonna be all right','','',521,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 13:59:42','Pending'),('EUWYACG','s.ramanujam@ericsson.com','Chennai','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,522,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:29:54','Pending'),('EARUSHI','arushi@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EKUMNIL','BUGS GSC EMM 4',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'EKUMNIL/EARUSHI_Res_64224649.mp4','To listen to others is the greatest respect you can give.',NULL,NULL,'','',523,'ESUJSIH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:11:11','Pending'),('EUXYBCO','p.raghu@ericsson.com','Bangalore','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,524,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 11:30:05','Pending'),('EMOHINT','mohd.intekhab@ericsson.com','Noida','EDURGAN','BUGS GSI Test Delivery Centre','','','','\r\nWe (Mohd Intekhab and Kush Kapoor) were asked to be part of the RNAM ECIL(Ericsson Common Integration Layer)  Project from CSI ADM TaaS Team on a short notice. We were asked to be at onsite in quick time of 4 days (since we had Visa\'s ready) and support in their on-going testing activities which had some strict deadlines and already under escalation from Customer (AT&T).\r\nWhen we were finally on boarded on the project and at the customer location, we had to be \"almost\" productive from day 1 and make sure we understand the in and outs of the customer system and all their testing requirements.\r\nThe project was already delayed and there were random code and implementation changes in terms of the \"Application under Test\".  \r\nThe task in hand was humongous as it involved provisioning 300 thousand subscribers over the network; and checking the network performance under peak loads. We knew we had a responsibility and challenge in hand. Over the next 3 weeks, we both collectively worked as a team day and night; almost in a 24X7 mode including weekends making sure we are fulfilling the customer expectations and reaching the required target in terms of project timelines. The result was we were able to successfully achieve the testing milestone and were greatly appreciated by the Region and Customer. Looking at our commitment, professional attitude and sense of ownership, we were asked to be a part of the team even in Phase 2 implementation. Even though both of us were working together on a project for the first time, we both had a sense of understanding for each other and the joint commitment helped us developed a feeling of trust and respect for each other. \r\nIt gave us a feeling of satisfaction for the respect and appreciation we both gained from the Region and the customer.\r\nTestimonial from Region\r\n1.	Bravo! Tom and the Scalability “Seal” Team. Excellent work indeed and outstanding dedication to give three weekends in a row to keep this project on track.\r\nPlease accept a note of appreciation on behalf of the AT&T CU. Thank you. Enjoy the weekend.\r\n2.	ECIL team – I guess these ‘Thank You’s are becoming monotonous. I really appreciate your dedication.\r\nHave a good well deserved weekend.\r\n\r\nFinally it felt great to be part of the Ericsson Family and living our Ericsson core values.\r\n','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,525,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 13:42:14','Pending'),('EBINKUR','binson.kuruvilla@ericsson.com','Pune','EDEKATK','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA Billing 1',NULL,NULL,'We spend a large volume of time from our daily lives at work. I personally consider it as a important part in the journey of life. Perseverance is one quality that I have seen & learnt while working in Ericsson. \r\nI joined EGI Pune in its initial days. EGI & specially the Pune location was just born & growing. There were lot of challenges at that point of time. Challenges in establishing teams, in projects allocation, keeping the employees involved, infrastructure and so on. But when i look at today we a lot more structured as a team, better in infrastructure, projects and things are continuing to move in a positive direction. In all this i can see the continuous & consistent attempt to improvise, no matter what the situation is. This is Perseverance. This definitely means a lot, as I can see things changing for the good. \r\nEven today there are challenges at different levels, but the attitude of Perseverance is the key to push ahead & win the situation.\r\n','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',526,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 14:22:09','Pending'),('EAKSENT','a.k.senthilkumar@ericsson.com','Chennai','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3','','','','I have joined Ericsson in Feb 2014 as a Solution Integrator. My first project is KSA SDP installation and integration. In this I almost transformed from a Ericsson beginner to expert by adhereing the Ericsson values. \r\n\r\nI am having a positive outlook and a ‘can do’ attitude. It may sound obvious but to complete a piece of work or have a specific responsibility it is essential that to get the job done. And not only complete it, but do so on time and to a high level of quality. As a professional I keep up my promises and where there is potential for something to take longer than anticipated or not achieve the desired standard or result, I managed expectations accordingly by keeping people well informed.\r\n\r\n\r\nIt is likely that I had to develop specialist knowledge and in some cases, undergone specific training and gained accreditation. Throughout my career it is essential to maintain my credibility and make a firm commitment to continuous professional development. This might mean simply keeping up to date with day to day developments within my area, working with my peers to support one another’s practice, or taking part in additional training and learning opportunities.\r\n\r\n\r\nThroughout my career I will face workplace challenges ranging from small day to day dilemmas to more complex problems. It is crucial that my approach is carefully thought out and my conduct remains appropriate at all times. If I am struggling with how to respond to a particular issue, I used to  consult a close colleague or workplace mentor for advice. ','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,527,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:03:47','Pending'),('EAKBHAT','akhil.b.bhatnagar@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ESONABH','BUGS GSI EMA 2','','','',NULL,'','','','','','','ESONABH/EAKBHAT_All_426345160.mp4','Acquiring and practicing a good value system',528,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:09:51','Pending'),('EKUMHEM','hemant.kumar@ericsson.com','Noida','ESAYGRG','BUGS GSI AFRICA CD TX 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,529,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:10:23','Pending'),('EMERJAI','merushikha.jain@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ESURDAS','BUGS GSI SDT R&D DU India PM',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,530,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:17:11','Pending'),('EKOLGOW','kolli.gowtham@ericsson.com','GURGAON','ESONABH','BUGS GSI EMA 2',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ESONABH/EKOLGOW_Per_840168223.mp4','Perseverance is the hard work you do after you get tired of doing the hard work you already did.','','',531,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:27:06','Pending'),('EMADHSU','sunil.b.madhwani@ericsson.com','Pune','EDEKATK','BUGS GSI CD-BSS PA Billing 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,532,'EAADMAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 12:53:10','Pending'),('ESACKAS','sachin.kashyap@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','EBPBPBP','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,533,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 13:03:51','Pending'),('EVEKODU','venkata.sameer.kumar.kodukula@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EJAVIPU','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 4','','','','Hi \r\nI am Venkata Sameer, a BSS Solution Architect associated with Ericsson for the past 3 years. \r\nTalking about E/// values, respect, perseverance and professionalism, I think they are much ingrained in the E/// way of working. \r\n\r\nRespect, \r\nI have come across a diverse nature of people during my stint with E///. Right from technical and managerial staff of Telecom Service Providers or for that matter any person from the industry, I could command a sense of respect & attention in their demeanor. So it is like this during our talks, ok you are from e///, ok now you have my attention lets talk further. \r\n\r\nPerseverance, \r\nWell, this trait is quite evident from the leadership position of E/// in the telecom vertical. We are the bandwidth leaders, network infrastructure innovators, and the industry bellweather. All this is because of the perseverance attitude of Ericssonites \r\n\r\nProfessionalism, \r\nI was once talking to a very senior leader from the practice that I am working in. One of the key takeaway of my conversation was that E/// get almost a lions share of customer repeat business for the practice. And this trait is associated with the professional attitude carried by its employees in their ways of working. \r\n\r\nSo it gives so much room for all the reasons to be associated with E/// \r\n\r\n','','','','','','','EJAVIPU/EVEKODU_All_592176229.avi','E /Professionalism / Perseverance / Respect',534,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 13:20:35','Completed'),('EAEFHIN','saravana.kumar.l@ericsson.com','Chennai','EBPBPBP','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 5',NULL,NULL,'I\'ve successfully completed Banglalink IN Swap project well before the timeline eventhough so many following barriers were there:\r\n1) continuous hardal \r\n    office cab was not available for so many months.  I went to customer office by walk / by rickshaw.  Two days, I went to Customer Site by ambulance due to the severe riot\r\n2) Day & Night Work \r\n     I\'ve worked day&night during the IN traffic migration time\r\n3) Car blasting\r\n     When I\'m working at the customer location, all of a sudden a car was torched by some vandals passing by on a motorcycle right in front of the office building.\r\n      Within minutes the car was completely engulfed in flames and the CNG cylinder burst with pieces of metals from the car’s roof and boot lid getting thrown up to as far as 30 feet into the air, a few of them hitting the glass panels on the 3rd floor of the office building. The main entrance glass door and panels of the Banglalink office building got damaged by the explosion.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EBPBPBP/EAEFHIN_Per_329912324.mpg','Successful Completion of Banglalink IN Swap Onsite Project, Dhaka, Bandladesh in hazardous situation','','',535,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 13:37:13','Pending'),('ESURRAY','r.surender@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EBPBPBP','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,536,'ESUJSIH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 13:38:49','Pending'),('EBANTAR','tarun.t.bansal@ericsson.com','Gurgaon','EKUMNIL','BUGS GSC EMM 4','The Campus to corporate training was a pillar for the core value of Ericsson\'s Professionalism. In that training, we were enlightened towards the etiquettes and behavior an individual must opt while working in any organisation. Scheduling of training (On site & offsite ) for the proper understanding of concept has also been a motivator to me for working\r\n','As far as I remember it was summer of 2014 when ericsson visited our campus, and everyone was excited as it was one of the most reputed company who visits our campus every year. I was excited too but there was a fear deep inside, what if I couldn\'t make it. It was a tough competition. Everyone\'s heart was beating fast, no one wanted to lose this opportunity. Ice was broken when the result was out and everyone was searching for their name in the list. Even I was searching for my name and finally arrived the moment of truth, I was selected. And since that day I actually started seeing respect in people\'s eye for me. And when I joined Ericsson we had a session on Ericsson values and when I saw respect as one of the core values, I thought I have been living this since I got selected.\r\n','During first day of my team introduction, I found my Line Manager as quite supportive person. After that new manager provides various opportunities to get involved with other team mates and their activities like Welcome party , OJT on Customer location which was very good learning experience for me. There is a very healthy and positive environment within the team which helps me in interacting and learning new things easily. from quite basic  things like accessing alex, RINA Homepage, Ericsson tools that have been used in daily activities like ESS/MSS,ITM,concur etc., which helps in creating a positive and workful environment. I feel very obliged by the support and help that i have got till time. Corporate life is difficult to understand and manage for a fresher but with My team\'s support and guidance, I have made it very comfortable.\r\n','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',537,'EPRISAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 13:47:09','Pending'),('EDHEKUR','dheeraj.kurianparambil@ericsson.com','Bangalore','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3','','','','I joined Ericsson 3 years back, and was instantly impressed with the values Ericsson,as an employer instill within each employee.\r\nOver the years, I have travelled across the globe representing Ericsson, and these values on display all over the office environment did help me portray the professional attitude required at each customer location and project.\r\n\r\nHere I want to share a story from Bharti Airtel India project.Eventhough I had worked for several project prior, there is a reason why I picked this one. Bharti Airtel India is one of the largest and challenging customer for Ericsson.And the project I worked for , is the Hardware modernaization project.All End Of Supports Sun-Solaris hardware were being replaced by HP-Linux.I was responsible for the SDP node.\r\nWe were a team of 7 Solution integrators.The customer had come up with an almost unrealistic target of making 30 SDPs LIVE  in nearly 2 months time, across 4 circles.THis requirement indeed challenged the credibility and trust on Ericsson for service delivery, and our CPM had entrusted us with the timely handover of these nodes.We were not sure If this could be achieved, but rather than saying NO, we decided to go ahead and give it a try.We were sure if we really stretch ourselves, even if not all 30 nodes, we knew we could come close,which was an achievement in itself.\r\nIt was a hard toil.As far as Bharti Airtel India is concerned, as much work you do, you have to do cordination as well.As it would be different teams handling different nodes.THere were days I was on call with atleast 4 teams, throughout the night.ANd I had to be available\r\n24 hours on call, as the node going LIVE is my node and the ownership is mine.I had to make hard choices between my personal and professional priorities during this period. over a month we slept 4-5 hours each day, also worked on weekends.At the end, we acheieved the target, with even 2 nodes going live each day.Even customer knew this was an unrealistic target, and was really satisfied with the fact that the goal was achieved.\r\n\r\nI strongly believe it is the values that I experienced and acquired observing other employees, that made me capable of acheiveing this feat , in this pressure scenario.I would continue to live with these values, and demonstrate them as an example to any other employee, so that they have the same positive effect that I had in challenging conditions.\r\n','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,538,'EANRDAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 14:20:18','Pending'),('EBHADIT','aditya.bhartiya@ericsson.com','Bangalore','ETHANGA','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,539,'EJALBAN',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 14:22:59','Pending'),('EGAUPIY','piyush.gautam@ericsson.com','Noida','EBARAJA','BUGS GSI BSS RINA CAC Support',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EBARAJA/EGAUPIY_Per_1081527967.mp4','Perseverance is determination;We all have dreams but to make them real it take lot of determination','','',540,'ECHAARU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 14:46:37','Pending'),('EEGIJKU','sathish.kumar.r@ericsson.com','Guindy Chennai','ERSRDHE','BUGS GSI CS CCN 1','Got continuous 97%+ SSAT feedback for all of my projects and in my recent project for Ooredoo-MBC, got very good appreciation from the region, CPM and form the customer.\r\nReference mails attached below \r\nHi ,\r\nCongrats to Sathish for the achievement .  Just to appraise you it was a 1 man show by Sathish but yes with support from GCH SA.\r\nIn continuation to the below we successfully tested the RO call scenarios which are working fine.\r\nThanks\r\nSambeet\r\n\r\nHi Sathish,\r\nVery impressed with your attitude and your approach.\r\nYou are now thinking like a SA and looking well ahead.\r\nWell done.\r\n\r\nVBR/     Wallis Dudhnath\r\nWell done Satish,\r\nWith your attitude and drive you can pick up and progress with any BSS (CS, EMM, OCC, etc..) delivery project.\r\nThank you.\r\nVBR/   Wallis\r\n\r\nExcellent Sathish,\r\nVery good work.\r\nYou are really helping to make Ooredoo-Kuwait’s MBC delivery a reference for GSC-I.\r\nWell done.\r\nVBR/   Wallis\r\n\r\nHi Ashutosh,\r\nFor Batelco please look and secure another profile tha',NULL,'Project: VoLTE with Huwaei TAS\r\n\r\nThe scope is to use VoLTE Ro based charging using OCC & SDP with Huwaei TAS as IMS core network for all of the existing traditional IN services like Voice, Video, call forwarding, Poke call, Reverse Charging, Communication Completion services, SMS , etc.\r\nChallenges Involved:\r\n•	E/// Ro development was based on with E/// MTAS and as of now E/// OCC nodes does not support integration with any other 3rd party TAS\r\n•	E/// OCC is not compatible with Huwaei properatory parameters for Ro charging\r\n•	So for each services there are lots of parameter’s (AVPs) (Both Huwaei properatory and E/// not supported 3GPP AVPs) coming in from Huwaei TAS which we have to map to our Ericsson charging context AVPs to make the charging work successfully.\r\nTechniques Applied:\r\n1. Using the SCE environment developed the adaptations to map the Huwaei Ro Parameters similar to that of sending by E/// MTAS to get it processed by OCC.\r\n2. This was done without any help from other re','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',541,'EPPPRRR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 14:59:34','Pending'),('ENIDGAR','nidhi.garg@ericsson.com','Noida','ESAYGOL','BUGS GSI MSDP-AO 2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,542,'EGANVIK',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-18 16:09:19','Pending'),('EMOISYE','moinuddin.m.syed@ericsson.com','Bangalore','EGAHCHN','BUGS GSC I 1st LA MBNL 3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,543,'EGANVAI',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 05:48:54','Pending'),('EGUVIVE','vivek.k.gupta@ericsson.com','GURGAON','EGANVAI','BUGS GSI OSS Adaptation',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,544,'ERANSIR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 07:05:49','Pending'),('EJNOORT','prabhu.m@ericsson.com','Chennai','EBPBPBP','BUGS GSI CS AIR SDP VS 5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,545,'EAADMAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 07:11:41','Pending'),('ESACBUR','sachin.v.burbure@ericsson.com','Pune','ETARDAS','BUGS GSI OSS CM-SF-OM-KOL1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,546,'ESUDHMU',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 09:56:40','Pending'),('EPARAMU','paramesha.muniyappa@ericsson.com','BANGALORE','ENARKHE','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn RNAM CA 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,547,'EGARBHA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 11:52:41','Pending'),('ENARKHE','narendra.sridharrao.khedgikar@ericsson.com','Bangalore','ERATBHA','BUGS GSI M&A Adaptn RNAM CA 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,548,'ESAADAS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 11:55:15','Pending');
